ion(),\\n../4649-a9dbf980/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/GenerateDynamicAccessReportInvocationTask.java:19: * generated JSON files under `build/native/nativeTestCompile/dynamic-access`.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/GenerateDynamicAccessReportInvocationTask.java:49:                .resolve(\\\"dynamic-access\\\");\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `fixes-native-image-run-fail` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR that fixes a native-image runtime failure for an existing library version update. Focus on validating the runtime/native fix, keeping the diff scoped, and ensuring dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previously tested version and the new version.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:9:These PRs repair metadata or tests after an existing library version compiles and builds a native image, but the native image fails when the test runs. Review them more lightly than `library-new-request` PRs: the library is already supported, so the goal is to restore native-image behavior for a newer version while preserving existing dynamic-access coverage.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:19:- Treat dynamic-access coverage preservation as the main quality gate. The new version should not report lower dynamic-access coverage than the previously tested version unless the PR gives a concrete, credible reason.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:20:- For numeric gates, compare the reported evidence as-is. Do not inspect generation filters, agent configuration, or metadata contents to second-guess why dynamic-access or metadata-count numbers are what they are.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:42:   - Accept narrow test edits that keep the same behavior covered across old and new versions.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:53:4. Check dynamic-access coverage across versions.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:55:   - Compare `dynamicAccess.coverageRatio`, `coveredCalls`, `totalCalls`, and the `dynamicAccess.breakdown` entries for reflection, resources, proxies, serialization, JNI, or any other present report type.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:56:   - Do not use `user-code-filter.json`, agent configuration, or metadata file contents to argue that the reported dynamic-access values are not comparable. Use the stats values as reported unless the stats are missing or stale.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:57:   - A lower `coverageRatio` or lower `coveredCalls` for the new version is blocking unless the total dynamic-access surface changed and the PR explains why the reduction is expected.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:58:   - If metadata fixes make the native run pass but the dynamic-access ratio drops, ask for restored coverage first. Passing native execution is not enough by itself.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:59:   - If `totalCalls` increases while `coveredCalls` stays flat or the ratio drops, ask for additional test coverage or metadata unless the uncovered calls are clearly outside the library behavior under test.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:67:   - Do not require an exact match. Differences are normal when upstream APIs move, generated metadata is cleaned up, or dynamic-access totals change.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:69:   - When the new total is below 25% of the original and the tests and dynamic-access stats still claim comparable coverage, ask for restored metadata or a concrete explanation of the API/package change.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:76:   - If CI is flaky but the diff and coverage comparison are sound, ask for a rerun instead of blocking on speculation.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:84:- Dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previous and new tested versions, or any apparent drop is convincingly explained by a changed upstream API surface.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:90:- The fix makes native execution pass by skipping the failing native path, disabling assertions, or removing coverage.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:91:- Dynamic-access coverage drops without a credible explanation and replacement coverage.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:100:- The API or native runtime change is plausible but the PR does not explain why a coverage drop is expected.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:107:- For coverage drops: say that dynamic-access coverage must not regress between tested versions, cite the old and new values, and ask for either restored coverage or a concrete explanation.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:109:- For native skips: say that the PR avoids the failing native path instead of fixing it, so it does not demonstrate native-image runtime coverage.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/model/DiscoveredArtifactMetadata.java:12: * Build-local discovered metadata for a single library coordinate.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/model/DiscoveredArtifactMetadata.java:14:public record DiscoveredArtifactMetadata(\\n../4649-a9dbf980/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/AnalyzeExternalLibraryDynamicAccessTask.java:43: * Resolves an arbitrary Maven coordinate and computes dynamic-access totals without repo-tracked tests.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/AnalyzeExternalLibraryDynamicAccessTask.java:67:                        \\\"reports/external-dynamic-access/summary.json\\\"\\n../4649-a9dbf980/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/AnalyzeExternalLibraryDynamicAccessTask.java:79:                .dir(\\\"tmp/external-dynamic-access/\\\" + sanitize(coordinates.toString()))\\n../4649-a9dbf980/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/AnalyzeExternalLibraryDynamicAccessTask.java:136:                imageDir.resolve(\\\"dynamic-access\\\")\\n../4649-a9dbf980/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/AbstractReadmeBadgeSummaryTask.java:53:        return getProject().getLayout().getBuildDirectory().dir(\\\"coverage-stats\\\").get().getAsFile().toPath();\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `fixes-javac-fail` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR that fixes Java compilation failures for an existing library version update. Focus on validating the compile fix, keeping the diff scoped, and ensuring dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previously tested version and the new version.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:9:These PRs repair test sources or test dependencies after an existing library is bumped and the new version no longer compiles with the old test code. Review them more lightly than `library-new-request` PRs: the library already exists, so the goal is to preserve working coverage across the version update rather than prove a brand-new metadata contribution from scratch.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:17:- Be more relaxed than `library-new-request`: do not reject only because a test resembles older coverage, stays in an existing package layout, or contains compatibility branches for multiple supported versions.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:18:- Do not accept changes that remove meaningful test coverage just to make `javac` pass.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:19:- Native-image execution should remain enabled by default when the repaired test reaches the native lane. Do not accept changes that skip or short-circuit native-image behavior. When a test exercises behavior that fundamentally relies on open-ended dynamic class loading that native image cannot support, such as loading classes, JARs, generated bytecode, plugin implementations, or other class definitions that are only discovered after the native executable is built, accept the `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(e)` catch pattern from `org.graalvm.internal.tck`. Reject raw native-only skips, bare `catch (Error)` blocks, and use of this pattern for ordinary reflection, resources, serialization, dynamic proxies, JNI, or missing reachability metadata.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:20:- Treat dynamic-access coverage preservation as the main quality gate. The new version should not report lower dynamic-access coverage than the previously tested version unless the PR gives a concrete, credible reason.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:21:- For numeric gates, compare the reported evidence as-is. Do not inspect generation filters, agent configuration, or metadata contents to second-guess why dynamic-access or metadata-count numbers are what they are.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:50:   - Compatibility branches are acceptable when they keep older and newer tested versions covered by the same test.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:54:4. Check dynamic-access coverage across versions.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:56:   - Compare `dynamicAccess.coverageRatio`, `coveredCalls`, `totalCalls`, and the `dynamicAccess.breakdown` entries for reflection, resources, proxies, serialization, JNI, or any other present report type.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:57:   - Do not use `user-code-filter.json`, agent configuration, or metadata file contents to argue that the reported dynamic-access values are not comparable. Use the stats values as reported unless the stats are missing or stale.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:58:   - A lower `coverageRatio` or lower `coveredCalls` for the new version is blocking unless the total dynamic-access surface changed and the PR explains why the reduction is expected.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:59:   - If `totalCalls` increases while `coveredCalls` stays flat or the ratio drops, ask for additional test coverage or metadata unless the uncovered calls are clearly outside the library behavior under test.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:67:   - Do not require an exact match. Differences are normal when upstream APIs move, generated metadata is cleaned up, or dynamic-access totals change.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:69:   - When the new total is below 25% of the original and the tests and dynamic-access stats still claim comparable coverage, ask for restored metadata or a concrete explanation of the API/package change.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:74:   - Prefer seeing the full target `test` lane green because a compile fix can still reduce runtime or native coverage.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:76:   - If CI is flaky but the diff and coverage comparison are sound, ask for a rerun instead of blocking on speculation.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:84:- Dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previous and new tested versions, or any apparent drop is convincingly explained by a changed upstream API surface.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:90:- The fix makes compilation pass by weakening or bypassing the test instead of adapting it to the changed API while preserving meaningful coverage.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:92:- Dynamic-access coverage drops without a credible explanation and replacement coverage.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:100:- The API change is plausible but the PR does not explain why a coverage drop is expected.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:107:- For coverage drops: say that dynamic-access coverage must not regress between tested versions, cite the old and new values, and ask for either restored coverage or a concrete explanation.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:109:- For deleted coverage: say that the PR fixes compilation by removing coverage and should instead adapt the test to the new API.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:110:- For native skips that does not depend on the open-ended dynamic class loading: say that the PR avoids the failing native path instead of fixing it, so it does not demonstrate native-image runtime coverage.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:121:- Bad compile repair that removes coverage:\\n../4649-a9dbf980/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:154:        // Expected: Native Image cannot load generated classes discovered after build.\\n../4649-a9dbf980/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/DiscoverArtifactMetadata.java:16:import org.graalvm.internal.tck.model.DiscoveredArtifactMetadata;\\n../4649-a9dbf980/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/DiscoverArtifactMetadata.java:93:      